narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This course created a broad, and useful, understanding of Structural Geology and it's underlying principles.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The practicality of the lectures was low, however the lab exercises were very useful. It would be good to list the class in the Blue Book as having a lab. This large additional time commitment was unexpected and was not referenced unless one looked at the syllabus.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: This course is an excellent introduction to structural geology. It covers the major topics which is claims to and does so by creating a useful background. The class creates not only a theoretical understanding but also a practical intuition about the topics at hand. A strong geology background prior to entering the course is very helpful.
